(219, 1, '2023-10-29 16:25:59', '2023-10-29 16:25:59', '<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-220 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Frame-1061-.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1539\" height=\"730\" />\n\n<b> 1.Christmas music show \"The Light\"</b>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Upbeat has been and will always be a source of immense pride for me. I\'ll never forget our very first public show at Purple Blues during Christmas, where we performed for a remarkable 2 hours and even took multiple song requests! It was such an enjoyable and memorable time. I\'m thrilled that we managed to have so much fun during a charity show. What\'s even more exciting is that we went on to host a SECOND charity show, which was an absolute blast in every sense of the word. Upbeat will forever hold a special place in my heart, rent-free. It marks my first live performance, in front of a diverse audience, alongside my friends.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Behind every live performance on the stage, the Upbeat band, comprising seven talented and charismatic individuals, will be the ambassadors of vibrant melodies and colorful sounds, promising spontaneity and musical brilliance.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As with all of Upbeat\'s projects, \"The Light Show\" is a fundraising endeavor through ticket sales. Upbeat commits to allocating all proceeds from the concert to contribute to the welfare of underprivileged children.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Upbeat\'s journey is one of music, camaraderie, and the joy of giving back, and it is an experience that I will cherish deeply.</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-222 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/IMG_1304-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" />\n\n<b>2.Performance of </b><b><i>Dan Tinh &amp; Then Singing</i></b><b> at the Vietnamese National Academy Of Music.</b>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the lyrical verses of the Tày people\'s \"Mùa hoa lê\" Then song, which I would loosely translate as \"In our village, the pear blossoms bloom, sparkling waters, the stream sings with delight,\" the joyful lyrics resonate with the gentle melodies of the Tính tẩu (Tày folk music) amidst the backdrop of Hanoi\'s landscapes. </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Then </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">singing has the power to dispel the chill of winter and transport listeners across the high mountains to the majestic landscapes of the Northwest.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The enchanting charm of Then singing lies in its simplicity, sincerity, accessibility, and emotive qualities. Listening to Then is an instant source of joy and delight. Moreover, the pure and poetic lyrics of Then depict the beauty of nature, love, and the homeland, often leaving one utterly captivated.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">UpBeat regularly participates in musical exchanges, collaborating with students, enthusiasts, and the Tày ethnic community at the National Academy of Music in Vietnam. Through our involvement, we hope to not only preserve and promote the Then tradition for those who cherish it but also actively engage with and perform at events organized by the Tày community in the capital.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With these initiatives, UpBeat aspires to connect and share the beauty of Then music, transcending boundaries and preserving the rich cultural heritage of the Tày people, and extending it to a broader audience, bringing the world closer to the enchanting rhythms of Tày folk music.</span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-224 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Frame-1123123u.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1539\" height=\"730\" />\n\n<b>3.A tour and performance of Dan Tinh - Then singing at Homestay Trieu Cuong</b>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I organized a cultural immersion trip for UpBeat Club members to provide them with a deep understanding of the Tày ethnic culture. The lush green surroundings, simple and peaceful way of life, and unique cultural aspects of the Tày people left a profound impression on everyone who visited this place.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Traveling along winding, picturesque roads and observing stilt houses nestled on the hillside, beneath the shade of cool trees, one could sense the serene life of the local inhabitants. Thượng Lâm Commune is not only renowned for its vast terraced fields but also as one of the cradles of the traditional Then singing style of the Tày ethnic group. Here, almost everyone can sing a few lines of Then songs, with many children as young as 6 or 7 years old participating in local Then singing clubs and Tính music ensembles within their village and commune.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">These young enthusiasts eagerly learn and strive to sing beautifully and authentically because it\'s a source of pride for their ethnic community. In the autumn, the atmosphere in the Thái Hải village is refreshing and mild. Sitting in a local wine house, listening to the Then song \"Tuyen Quang yêu thương,\" sung from the heart and filled with the emotions of the locals, with a cup of fragrant, sticky rice wine in hand, one can feel the rustic yet profound sentiments of the people living in this region.</span>', 'President · UPBEAT<br>(Oct 2021 - Sep 2023)', 'A self-driving car trained by thousands of video recordings,  driving and turning automatically based on a path which was my first AI product I created in my career path in technology. I applied to a self-driving car project designed by Founder GotIt and chief architect Gabi Zuniga in 2016', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '166-autosave-v1', '', '', '2023-10-29 16:25:59', '2023-10-29 16:25:59', '', 166, 'http://localhost/trasua/?p=219', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
