(291, 1, '2023-10-30 16:27:40', '2023-10-30 16:27:40', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt;\"><b>1.STEAM for Vietnam: Not Missing Out on the Talented \"Little Engineer\"</b></span></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nhttps://youtu.be/5u1SZCWxq-o?si=H6RqDTxclcVIDTSo\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Gabi Zuniga, who is over 50 years old, is the Principal Architect of Got It in the \"holy\" Silicon Valley. Having previously worked for IBM Watson, he decided to join Got It approximately three years ago and frequently commutes between the United States and Vietnam to work with Got It\'s team in Vietnam.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In a recent visit, he was pleasantly surprised to find a young boy walking around the Got It Vietnam office. He was curious and had many questions!</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-160 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/ex-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"954\" height=\"480\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The young boy was Tuan Anh, who is only 13 years old. Last year, he became the youngest software engineering intern at Got It. On his first day, he had just graduated from the 7th grade. In a little over three months, Tuan Anh completed an impressive university-level course and even worked on a self-driving car project.\"My mom knew I was interested in programming and started looking for anything related to it that I could do online. She stumbled upon Got It. My mom asked her friends how Got It worked and managed to arrange an interview for me, which led to my internship here,\" Tuan Anh shared with Gabi Zuniga. Before joining Got It, Tuan Anh had some knowledge of web design, including HTML, CSS, and a bit of JavaScript. However, at Got It, he learned much more about programming languages, especially Python, and completed a course using American university-level materials. He also delved into artificial intelligence and applied it to a challenging project, creating a mini self-driving car in a learn-as-you-go style.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In addition to his technical skills, Tuấn Anh focused on improving his English and soft skills to work and communicate effectively with colleagues from diverse cultural backgrounds. He emphasized that his goal was to build a solid foundation for the future rather than winning competitions or impressing his mother.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\"This kid is truly amazing!\" Gabi Zuniga exclaimed in surprise as he listened to Tuan Anh\'s story of learning and creating a software-based self-driving car with guidance from Got It\'s engineers.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt;\"><b>2.Mr. Hung Tran - My AI Teacher and Hero at Got It</b></span></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=el90HTd549I\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dr. Tran Viet Hung, 41 years old, is the founder of Got It, a technology startup that has raised $25 million in investment and is headquartered in Silicon Valley, USA. One summer day in 2019, he received a letter requesting an internship at Got It from a 13-year-old boy. Despite having only a bit of programming knowledge, the young boy desired to gain real-world experience as a programmer during his summer break. Seeing a reflection of his younger self in the boy, Dr. Hung decided to accept him as an intern and provide additional training. Having previously taught university students, Dr. Hung experimented by using American university-level materials to educate the young boy.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-162 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/ex-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"954\" height=\"480\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For the boy\'s \"graduation project,\" which involved creating a self-driving car with artificial intelligence, Dr. Hung purchased a remote-controlled car, removed all of its components, replaced them with a Raspberry Pi circuit board, and connected it to a small camera. He and the engineers at Got It then guided the young boy in collecting data to train AI models and enable AI to control the car. Eventually, the car could drive itself, leaving many people astonished.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\"Kids these days are quite remarkable. If they are given early access to technology, they will develop and have a very bright future,\" Dr. Hung thought, and he aspired to do something for the youth of Vietnam.</p>', 'Youngest Talented Intern in Vietnam at Global Technology Company, Got It AI.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'youngest-talented-trainee-in-vietnam-at-global-technology-company-got-it-ai', '', '', '2023-11-02 03:01:00', '2023-11-02 03:01:00', '', 0, 'http://localhost/trasua/?p=291', 0, 'post', '', 0),
