(333, 1, '2023-10-30 17:10:06', '2023-10-30 17:10:06', '<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-220 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Frame-1061-.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1539\" height=\"730\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt;\"><strong> 1.Christmas music show \"The Light\"</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Upbeat has been and will always be a source of immense pride for me. I\'ll never forget our very first public show at Purple Blues during Christmas, where we performed for a remarkable 2 hours and even took multiple song requests! It was such an enjoyable and memorable time. I\'m thrilled that we managed to have so much fun during a charity show. What\'s even more exciting is that we went on to host a SECOND charity show, which was an absolute blast in every sense of the word. Upbeat will forever hold a special place in my heart, rent-free. It marks my first live performance, in front of a diverse audience, alongside my friends.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Behind every live performance on the stage, the Upbeat band, comprising seven talented and charismatic individuals, will be the ambassadors of vibrant melodies and colorful sounds, promising spontaneity and musical brilliance.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">As with all of Upbeat\'s projects, \"The Light Show\" is a fundraising endeavor through ticket sales. Upbeat commits to allocating all proceeds from the concert to contribute to the welfare of underprivileged children.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Upbeat\'s journey is one of music, camaraderie, and the joy of giving back, and it is an experience that I will cherish deeply.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-222 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/IMG_1304-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt;\"><strong>2.Performance of Dan Tinh &amp; Then Singing at the Vietnamese National Academy Of Music.</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">In the lyrical verses of the Tày people\'s \"Mùa hoa lê\" Then song, which I would loosely translate as \"In our village, the pear blossoms bloom, sparkling waters, the stream sings with delight,\" the joyful lyrics resonate with the gentle melodies of the Tính tẩu (Tày folk music) amidst the backdrop of Hanoi\'s landscapes. <i>Then </i>singing has the power to dispel the chill of winter and transport listeners across the high mountains to the majestic landscapes of the Northwest.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The enchanting charm of Then singing lies in its simplicity, sincerity, accessibility, and emotive qualities. Listening to Then is an instant source of joy and delight. Moreover, the pure and poetic lyrics of Then depict the beauty of nature, love, and the homeland, often leaving one utterly captivated.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">UpBeat regularly participates in musical exchanges, collaborating with students, enthusiasts, and the Tày ethnic community at the National Academy of Music in Vietnam. Through our involvement, we hope to not only preserve and promote the Then tradition for those who cherish it but also actively engage with and perform at events organized by the Tày community in the capital.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">With these initiatives, UpBeat aspires to connect and share the beauty of Then music, transcending boundaries and preserving the rich cultural heritage of the Tày people, and extending it to a broader audience, bringing the world closer to the enchanting rhythms of Tày folk music.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-224 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Frame-1123123u.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1539\" height=\"730\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt;\"><strong>3.A tour and performance of Dan Tinh\r\nThen singing at Homestay Trieu Cuong</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">I organized a cultural immersion trip for UpBeat Club members to provide them with a deep understanding of the Tày ethnic culture. The lush green surroundings, simple and peaceful way of life, and unique cultural aspects of the Tày people left a profound impression on everyone who visited this place.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Traveling along winding, picturesque roads and observing stilt houses nestled on the hillside, beneath the shade of cool trees, one could sense the serene life of the local inhabitants. Thượng Lâm Commune is not only renowned for its vast terraced fields but also as one of the cradles of the traditional Then singing style of the Tày ethnic group. Here, almost everyone can sing a few lines of Then songs, with many children as young as 6 or 7 years old participating in local Then singing clubs and Tính music ensembles within their village and commune.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">These young enthusiasts eagerly learn and strive to sing beautifully and authentically because it\'s a source of pride for their ethnic community. In the autumn, the atmosphere in the Thái Hải village is refreshing and mild. Sitting in a local wine house, listening to the Then song \"Tuyen Quang yêu thương,\" sung from the heart and filled with the emotions of the locals, with a cup of fragrant, sticky rice wine in hand, one can feel the rustic yet profound sentiments of the people living in this region.</p>', 'President · UPBEAT (Oct 2021 - Sep 2023)', 'With our first series of activities, I and the Greenwave team aimed to launch a small campaign, a simple yet impactful action – planting an additional tree in all the gardens, balconies, schoolyards, offices, which we call \"Bringing Back the Green.\"', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '166-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-10-30 17:10:06', '2023-10-30 17:10:06', '', 166, 'http://localhost/trasua/?p=333', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(334, 1, '2023-10-30 17:10:27', '2023-10-30 17:10:27', '<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-211 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/366586477_197940783271746_2464261500335916016_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1178\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt;\"><strong>1.Workshop AI Experience:\r\nThe Age of Artificial Intelligence</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">In the context of the ongoing efforts within the education and scientific communities, the Online STEM Topic Workshop took place on June 11th, attracting the participation of hundreds of enthusiasts and those interested in the field of STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics) from around the world. The event provided a day full of information, knowledge sharing, and learning opportunities from reputable speakers in the field.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Speaker Tran Minh Quang kicked off the event with an engaging presentation on the importance of STEM in modern and future life. He emphasized the decisive role of STEM in addressing global challenges and exploring new potentials.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The workshop concluded with an interactive session with the audience, allowing them to ask questions and exchange opinions with the speakers. The event helped create an open environment for sharing knowledge and connecting individuals interested in STEM.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">In a world filled with challenges and opportunities, the Online STEM Topic Workshop, featuring top speakers, has contributed to the advancement of this field, and it is hoped that it will continue to pave the way for new developments in the future.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-213 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Frame-1057.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1539\" height=\"753\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt;\"><strong>2.STEMPIRE Science Day 2023\r\nScience Exhibition</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The STEMpire Club was established with a mission to popularize STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics) and engineering sciences among passionate and curious students. We also aspire to make meaningful contributions to our community and connect with like-minded students. Simply put, we aim to create an environment where students can satisfy their scientific passions.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">In pursuit of this goal, our club members collaborated to develop a program that included an exhibition showcasing scientific and engineering products and a collaborative effort to build a library with Phan Thiết Middle School.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Through these activities, STEMpire Club aimed to provide an incredible experience for the participating students. They had the opportunity to use and experience scientific and technological products like automated robots, electronic circuits, and artificial intelligence systems, all guided by STEMpire Club members. Notably, after experiencing these scientific products, STEMpire Club gifted Phan Thiết Middle School a model of a smart solar-powered house, constructed, designed, and programmed by our very own club members.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Furthermore, STEMpire Club was pleased to provide the school with English books and a desktop computer, all in an effort to support the school in building its library. We hope that this support will aid the school and its students in more effectively engaging with STEM subjects and sparking a passion for learning, research, and exploration in the field of science and engineering.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-214 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Frame-1058.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1539\" height=\"730\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt;\"><strong>3.<span class=\"Y2IQFc\" lang=\"en\">Visit Tuyen Quang Hydroelectric Plant</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The visit to the Tuyen Quang hydropower plant was truly an incredible and memorable experience for me. Right from the beginning, we were able to witness significant structures such as water reservoirs and the processing plant. Our expert guide explained how the machinery operates and how it generates electrical energy.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The most remarkable part of the tour was when we got up close and personal with the working turbines. The feeling of seeing hydropower in action, transforming water into electricity, is beyond words. It deepened our understanding of the necessity of this technology and the vital role it plays in providing electricity to millions of people.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Thanks to this trip, we gained a more profound insight into the electricity industry and renewable energy sources. We left feeling inspired and more conscious of the importance of environmental conservation and optimizing the use of renewable energy sources.</p>', 'Co-Founder of  STEMPIRE Club <br> (Nov 2022 - Now)', 'In the context of the ongoing efforts within the education and scientific communities, the Online STEM Topic Workshop took place on June 11th, attracting the participation of hundreds of enthusiasts and those interested in the field of STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics) from around the world. The event provided a day full of information, knowledge sharing, and learning opportunities from reputable speakers in the field.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '170-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-10-30 17:10:27', '2023-10-30 17:10:27', '', 170, 'http://localhost/trasua/?p=334', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(335, 1, '2023-10-30 17:11:04', '2023-10-30 17:11:04', '<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-196 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/352198155_761321225780566_2282037430624259009_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1367\" />\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt;\"><strong>1.Gree</strong><strong>n Land Returns Event</strong></span></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">With our first series of activities, I and the Greenwave team aimed to launch a small campaign, a simple yet impactful action – planting an additional tree in all the gardens, balconies, schoolyards, offices, which we call \"Bringing Back the Green.\"</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">At our first destination, Greenwave collaborated with three projects to organize a Children\'s Day event and gave nearly 50 pots of plants and 50 gifts to children with specific disabilities, particularly at the Thuy An Functional Rehabilitation Center for People with Disabilities in Ba Vi.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/IMG_7197.tif\" alt=\"\" /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/IMG_7197.tif\" alt=\"\" /><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-199 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/IMG_7197.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1399\" height=\"928\" />\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt;\"><strong>2.Trash\'s Journey Event</strong></span></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Making a stop at the fair combined with the PLASTIVAL plastic exhibition is an ideal choice to create a space filled with colors, where children can have fun during the weekend and unleash their creativity in recycling plastic products.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Through this event, Greenwave aims to provide motivation for everyone to join hands in environmental protection, recycling, and transforming unique plastic recycling models, thereby helping the environment come back to life, greener than ever before</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-205 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Frame-1056.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1539\" height=\"753\" />\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt;\"><strong>3.Green Land Returns Event</strong></span></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">With our first series of activities, I and the Greenwave team aimed to launch a small campaign, a simple yet impactful action – planting an additional tree in all the gardens, balconies, schoolyards, offices, which we call \"Bringing Back the Green.\"</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">At our first destination, Greenwave collaborated with three projects to organize a Children\'s Day event and gave nearly 50 pots of plants and 50 gifts to children with specific disabilities, particularly at the Thuy An Functional Rehabilitation Center for People with Disabilities in Ba Vi.</p>', 'Founder & President · Greenwave Club (Dec 2021 - Now)', 'With our first series of activities, I and the Greenwave team aimed to launch a small campaign, a simple yet impactful action – planting an additional tree in all the gardens, balconies, schoolyards, offices, which we call \"Bringing Back the Green.\"', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '171-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-10-30 17:11:04', '2023-10-30 17:11:04', '', 171, 'http://localhost/trasua/?p=335', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(336, 1, '2023-10-30 17:12:30', '2023-10-30 17:12:30', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt;\"><b>1.STEAM for Vietnam: Not Missing Out on the Talented \"Little Engineer\"</b></span></p>\r\nhttps://youtu.be/5u1SZCWxq-o?si=H6RqDTxclcVIDTSo\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Gabi Zuniga, who is over 50 years old, is the Principal Architect of Got It in the \"holy\" Silicon Valley. Having previously worked for IBM Watson, he decided to join Got It approximately three years ago and frequently commutes between the United States and Vietnam to work with Got It\'s team in Vietnam.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In a recent visit, he was pleasantly surprised to find a young boy walking around the Got It Vietnam office. He was curious and had many questions!</p>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-160 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/ex-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"954\" height=\"480\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The young boy was Tuấn Anh, who is only 13 years old. Last year, he became the youngest software engineering intern at Got It. On his first day, he had just graduated from the 7th grade. In a little over three months, Tuấn Anh completed an impressive university-level course and even worked on a self-driving car project.\"My mom knew I was interested in programming and started looking for anything related to it that I could do online. She stumbled upon Got It. My mom asked her friends how Got It worked and managed to arrange an interview for me, which led to my internship here,\" Tuấn Anh shared with Gabi Zuniga. Before joining Got It, Tuấn Anh had some knowledge of web design, including HTML, CSS, and a bit of JavaScript. However, at Got It, he learned much more about programming languages, especially Python, and completed a course using American university-level materials. He also delved into artificial intelligence and applied it to a challenging project, creating a mini self-driving car in a learn-as-you-go style.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In addition to his technical skills, Tuấn Anh focused on improving his English and soft skills to work and communicate effectively with colleagues from diverse cultural backgrounds. He emphasized that his goal was to build a solid foundation for the future rather than winning competitions or impressing his mother.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">\"This kid is truly amazing!\" Gabi Zuniga exclaimed in surprise as he listened to Tuấn Anh\'s story of learning and creating a software-based self-driving car with guidance from Got It\'s engineers.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt;\"><b>2.Mr. Hung Tran - My AI Teacher and Hero at Got It</b></span></p>\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=el90HTd549I\r\n\r\nDr. Trần Việt Hùng, 41 years old, is the founder of Got It, a technology startup that has raised $25 million in investment and is headquartered in Silicon Valley, USA. One summer day in 2019, he received a letter requesting an internship at Got It from a 13-year-old boy. Despite having only a bit of programming knowledge, the young boy desired to gain real-world experience as a programmer during his summer break. Seeing a reflection of his younger self in the boy, Dr. Hùng decided to accept him as an intern and provide additional training. Having previously taught university students, Dr. Hùng experimented by using American university-level materials to educate the young boy.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-162 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/ex-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"954\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\nFor the boy\'s \"graduation project,\" which involved creating a self-driving car with artificial intelligence, Dr. Hùng purchased a remote-controlled car, removed all of its components, replaced them with a Raspberry Pi circuit board, and connected it to a small camera. He and the engineers at Got It then guided the young boy in collecting data to train AI models and enable AI to control the car. Eventually, the car could drive itself, leaving many people astonished.\r\n\r\n\"Kids these days are quite remarkable. If they are given early access to technology, they will develop and have a very bright future,\" Dr. Hùng thought, and he aspired to do something for the youth of Vietnam.', 'Youngest Talented Trainee in Vietnam at Global Technology Company, Got It AI.', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '291-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-10-30 17:12:30', '2023-10-30 17:12:30', '', 291, 'http://localhost/trasua/?p=336', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
