(357, 1, '2023-10-31 10:40:28', '2023-10-31 10:40:28', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-185 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-3-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"954\" height=\"480\" />\r\n</span>\r\nEmbarking on an internship journey at Got It, Inc. as an AI intern was not just a stepping stone in my career; it was a profound learning experience that left a lasting impact on my professional growth. Over the course of my internship, I had the privilege of delving into the world of Artificial Intelligence, where I honed my skills, deepened my knowledge, and played a pivotal role in the organization\'s ongoing success.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Enhancing Python Programming Skills</strong></span>\r\nOne of the central pillars of my internship was the significant improvement in my Python programming skills. As a fundamental language for AI development, Python is the linchpin of numerous AI projects. During my tenure at Got It, Inc., I had the opportunity to write code that was both functional and efficient. This journey involved mastering Python libraries, frameworks, and, most importantly, the best practices for Python development. The experience allowed me to bridge the gap between theoretical knowledge and practical application, furthering my understanding of the language\'s intricacies.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>The Art of Problem-Solving and Organization</strong></span>\r\nAI development is often akin to solving intricate puzzles, and my internship honed my problem-solving abilities. The projects I worked on presented multifaceted challenges that required creative and analytical thinking. These experiences not only tested my skills but also broadened my problem-solving repertoire. I learned to analyze data, develop algorithms, and troubleshoot issues as they arose, a skill set that extends far beyond AI into everyday problem-solving.\r\n\r\nAnother vital aspect of my internship was organization. In the fast-paced world of AI development, maintaining order and structure is essential. I was responsible for managing data, code, and project-related documents. Effective organization streamlined the development process, making it more efficient and enabling our team to work seamlessly.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-314 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/image-8-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1539\" height=\"730\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Mastering Jupyter Notebook and Visual Studio Code</strong></span>\r\nThe world of AI is intrinsically tied to powerful tools, and my internship introduced me to two invaluable ones - Jupyter Notebook and Visual Studio Code. Jupyter Notebook became my trusted companion for interactive data analysis and reporting. Its versatility allowed me to explore data and present findings in an engaging and informative manner. Visual Studio Code, on the other hand, became my go-to platform for code development, debugging, and version control. These tools not only facilitated my work but also accelerated my learning curve, allowing me to be more productive and collaborative.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Testing and Suggesting Improvements</strong></span>\r\nAs an AI intern, I had the responsibility of rigorously testing applications and AI products. This task was a crucial step in ensuring the quality and performance of the projects we were working on. I was not just identifying issues and bugs but also actively contributing by suggesting improvements. This hands-on experience enabled me to understand the importance of quality assurance in AI and the iterative nature of development.\r\n\r\nMy internship at Got It, Inc. was a transformative journey that allowed me to evolve as an AI professional. It was a unique blend of learning and contribution, where I not only improved my Python programming skills, honed my problem-solving abilities, and mastered essential AI tools but also actively participated in the development and enhancement of AI applications. This experience has left an indelible mark on my career and has ignited a continued passion for the limitless possibilities of Artificial Intelligence. I am deeply grateful for the opportunity and look forward to applying the knowledge and skills I gained during this internship in my future endeavors.', 'AI Intern at  Global Technology Company, Got it', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '310-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-10-31 10:40:28', '2023-10-31 10:40:28', '', 310, 'http://localhost/trasua/?p=357', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(358, 1, '2023-10-31 10:40:47', '2023-10-31 10:40:47', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt;\"><b>1.STEAM for Vietnam: Not Missing Out on the Talented \"Little Engineer\"</b></span></p>\r\nhttps://youtu.be/5u1SZCWxq-o?si=H6RqDTxclcVIDTSo\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Gabi Zuniga, who is over 50 years old, is the Principal Architect of Got It in the \"holy\" Silicon Valley. Having previously worked for IBM Watson, he decided to join Got It approximately three years ago and frequently commutes between the United States and Vietnam to work with Got It\'s team in Vietnam.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In a recent visit, he was pleasantly surprised to find a young boy walking around the Got It Vietnam office. He was curious and had many questions!</p>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-160 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/ex-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"954\" height=\"480\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The young boy was Tuan Anh, who is only 13 years old. Last year, he became the youngest software engineering intern at Got It. On his first day, he had just graduated from the 7th grade. In a little over three months, Tuan Anh completed an impressive university-level course and even worked on a self-driving car project.\"My mom knew I was interested in programming and started looking for anything related to it that I could do online. She stumbled upon Got It. My mom asked her friends how Got It worked and managed to arrange an interview for me, which led to my internship here,\" Tuan Anh shared with Gabi Zuniga. Before joining Got It, Tuan Anh had some knowledge of web design, including HTML, CSS, and a bit of JavaScript. However, at Got It, he learned much more about programming languages, especially Python, and completed a course using American university-level materials. He also delved into artificial intelligence and applied it to a challenging project, creating a mini self-driving car in a learn-as-you-go style.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">In addition to his technical skills, Tuấn Anh focused on improving his English and soft skills to work and communicate effectively with colleagues from diverse cultural backgrounds. He emphasized that his goal was to build a solid foundation for the future rather than winning competitions or impressing his mother.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">\"This kid is truly amazing!\" Gabi Zuniga exclaimed in surprise as he listened to Tuan Anh\'s story of learning and creating a software-based self-driving car with guidance from Got It\'s engineers.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36pt;\"><b>2.Mr. Hung Tran - My AI Teacher and Hero at Got It</b></span></p>\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=el90HTd549I\r\n\r\nDr. Tran Viet Hung, 41 years old, is the founder of Got It, a technology startup that has raised $25 million in investment and is headquartered in Silicon Valley, USA. One summer day in 2019, he received a letter requesting an internship at Got It from a 13-year-old boy. Despite having only a bit of programming knowledge, the young boy desired to gain real-world experience as a programmer during his summer break. Seeing a reflection of his younger self in the boy, Dr. Hung decided to accept him as an intern and provide additional training. Having previously taught university students, Dr. Hùng experimented by using American university-level materials to educate the young boy.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-162 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/ex-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"954\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\nFor the boy\'s \"graduation project,\" which involved creating a self-driving car with artificial intelligence, Dr. Hung purchased a remote-controlled car, removed all of its components, replaced them with a Raspberry Pi circuit board, and connected it to a small camera. He and the engineers at Got It then guided the young boy in collecting data to train AI models and enable AI to control the car. Eventually, the car could drive itself, leaving many people astonished.\r\n\r\n\"Kids these days are quite remarkable. If they are given early access to technology, they will develop and have a very bright future,\" Dr. Hung thought, and he aspired to do something for the youth of Vietnam.', 'Youngest Talented Trainee in Vietnam at Global Technology Company, Got it AI.', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '291-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-10-31 10:40:47', '2023-10-31 10:40:47', '', 291, 'http://localhost/trasua/?p=358', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
